==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water gilding
<hw>Wa"ter gild"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>The act, or the process, of
gilding metallic surfaces by covering them with a thin coating of
amalgam of gold, and then volatilizing the mercury by heat; -- called
also <altname>wash gilding</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water glass</ent>⟦br⟧
